## R6 — Weak or absent cross-domain signal

**What it is**

The thesis assumes that understanding someone's taste in one domain (e.g., movies) meaningfully improves recommendations in an unrelated domain (e.g., restaurants). This is an assumption, not a validated fact.

**Why it matters**

If cross-domain signal turns out to be weak, the entire premise of PDE over a single excellent single-domain app collapses — the extra complexity of the Interest Graph would not translate into extra recommendation quality.

**How we would detect it**

Once there are two mini apps with real usage data, measure whether adding data from domain B measurably improves recommendation quality/acceptance in domain A, compared to a single-domain baseline.

**What would reduce it**

This can only really be tested once two data-generating mini apps exist. Until then, treat cross-domain lift as an unproven hypothesis — do not architect for it prematurely (see R4).

**Status:** Cannot be tested yet. Flagged so it isn't forgotten or assumed true by default.

